---
title: Roasted Veggie & Lentil Jumble with Feta, Toasted Almonds and Herby Drizzle
description: The nature of a jumble is to mix all the ingredients for a beautiful blend of flavours. Our roasted veg and lentil variation is a Middle-Eastern inspired dish made with sweet and fragrant spices and a slight kick of heat thanks to the chilli. Sweet potato, aubergine and tomatoes are a great match for the earthy and nutty flavour of lentils. Finish off with a sprinkling of tart feta mixed with lemon and toasted almonds.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/roasted-veggie-lentil-jumble-69bfec2c-16875e0b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/roasted-veggie-lentil-jumble-5d415e96e203d2000d5668c7-9d2cd696.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 463 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 53 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 20 g
  sodium: 2 g
  serving size: 671
time required: 45m
course: main course
author: Mimi Morley
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/roasted-veggie-lentil-jumble-5d415e96e203d2000d5668c7
servings: 2
---

Preheat the oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1}, then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 3cm pieces. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Cut one half into 3 wedges, thinly slice the other half. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the sweet potato, aubergine and onion wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} then sprinkle over the @ras-el-hanout{1} and a pinch of @chilli flakes{1/2%tsp} (careful they're hot!). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Halfway through cooking, turn the veg, then add the tomatoes to the tray to roast for the remaining ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, crumble the @feta cheese{100} into small pieces. Zest the @lemon{1/2}, cut into wedges. Finely chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all), drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{12.5} and toast until lightly brown, ~{2-3%minutes}, stirring regularly (don't take your eye off them!). Remove the almonds to a #bowl{} and set aside (we'll use the pan again in a second!).

Squeeze the lemon juice into a bowl and add a glug of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the coriander and mix together. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the frying pan on medium high heat, add the sliced onion and cook until soft, ~{5-6%minutes}, stir occasionally. Add the garlic and @ground cumin{2} to the onion, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{75} and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil, simmer until the water has reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the lentils cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Once the veg has finished cooking, remove from the oven and tip the lentils into the tray. Add the lemon zest to the tray and mix everything together. Serve into large #bowls{}, with the feta and toasted almonds sprinkled on top. Spoon over the herby drizzle and add another pinch of chilli if you want to! Serve any remaining lemon wedges on the side. Enjoy!